PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1771941809
OL,3,CCould a tampon help detect early signs
OL,4,Cof cancer?
OL,6,FThe VIOLET study involves taking
OL,7,Fsamples of vaginal fluid from women
OL,8,Fwho are undergoing surgery for
OL,9,Fsuspected or confirmed ovarian cancer.
OL,11,FThe samples are then compared with
OL,12,Fthose from healthy volunteers. The
OL,13,Fteam will then look for changes
OL,14,Fpresent in both the cancer cells and
OL,15,Fthe vaginal fluid.
OL,17,FAccording to Cancer Research UK, on
OL,18,Faverage, 21 women a day are diagnosed
OL,19,Fwith ovarian cancer. However only
OL,20,Faround a quarter of cases are caught
OL,21,Fin the early stages.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
